comments: I am a pretty avid chess player so I am used to playing with AI/engines like leela or stockfish. I would suggest maybe having the computer opponent play in different ways each game. This reminded me of lower strength stockfish, especially when servers are busy on lichess. The lower strength Stockfish will sometimes get "stuck" and play the same moves each game ,and once you know the pattern, you can beat it in the same manner over and over again. I recognized after game two my opponent was just going to do the same thing over and over again and the recommendation system would defeat it each time.
I didn't notice any errors or typos and had no issues at all, thanks!
